commText: Welcome back. CSK have their impact player - Shardul Thakur in. Dube out. Chahar with a wide slip.

Mitchell: We'll take that score. There's a little bit of dew around and we'll have to bowl well. Back ourselves to get the job done. It was about trying to keep putting pressure. Knew the pitch would be slightly slow. It's a new wicket. We'll throw ourselves around (on the field) and try to get the job done. He's a beautiful player to watch (Gaikwad).

21:25 Local Time, 15:55 GMT, 21:25 IST: CSK once again go past 200. Last game here against LSG they made 210 and lost. Tonight they have got 212, will that be enough? Coming back to this innings, it was again the Gaikwad show with contributions from Mitchell and Shivam Dube. Rahane fell early but Gaikwad and Mitchell strung together a 107-run stand. Mitchell who hasn't fired at all this season made a timely return to form with his first fifty in the IPL. But it was the CSK skipper though who was the star. Yet another attractive innings and he looked set for consecutive tons till the heat and humidity of Chennai sapped all his energy and by the end of his knock, he was visibly tired and his dismissal was a tired shot. Dube did his job and once again MS did what he does always - come out to milk the crowd and give them what they want - despite facing just 2 balls. Excellent last two overs for SRH as only 20 came off it. Will that be the difference? Let's find out when we are back for the chase in 5 minutes...
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, Shivam Dube swings hard and the thick outside-edge is on the bounce, short third man dives to his right and stops it. CSK end at 212
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, SIX, low full-toss on the stumps, flicked and it's high and handsome over deep mid-wicket, flies away. Crucial six for CSK
T Natarajan to Dhoni, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Dhoni mistimes the pull to deep square leg

T Natarajan to Dhoni, FOUR, was half a chance at deep square leg and credit to the fielder who went for it. A low full-toss on the stumps, flicked in the air and Abhishek was the man, dives forward but the ball bounces just in front of the right hand and goes under it, runs away for four and again the crowd go bonkers
First time a batter got out in nineties this season
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease

And guess who has come out for the crowd to lose their minds. MSD. Yet another night that most people won't ever forget. You have to hear the noise to believe it. Yellow flags being waved. Whistles being tooted. Shouting, screeching and what not! I0$ Forcing them to switch off their brains till he is there.

T Natarajan to Gaikwad, out Caught by Nitish Reddy!! Gaikwad falls for 98. A slower ball full on the stumps, Gaikwad does not get under it for the loft, miscues it and it's down deep mid-wicket's throat. Nitish makes no mistake. Gaikwad shakes his head as he walks back for 98. Fine innings nonetheless. Gaikwad c Nitish Reddy b T Natarajan 98(54) [4s-10 6s-3]
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Unadkat to Gaikwad, 2 runs, Cummins had he sent a better throw, Gaikwad was gone. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to point and Cummins threw it hard and wide of the stumps and the bowler couldn't get across in time, Gaikwad had given up by then, no backing up and they take one more

Cummins to Gaikwad, 2 runs, slower ball off-cutter full outside off, Gaikwad toe-ends the loft and just clears extra-cover running back

Cummins to Shivam Dube, SIX, smashed. A wide slower ball off-cutter outside off on a good length, Shivam Dube gets across and pummels it straight down the ground. Unreal power

T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, SIX, that's the power of Shivam Dube. A low full-toss outside off, he gets forward and lofts with an open face, flies over deep extra-cover. Went 80m

Natarajan round the wicket now.

T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, great attempt at a caught and bowled. Natarajan runs forward and dives, gets a hand on it, but fails to hang on. Full and at the pads, Shivam Dube heaves and the thick inside-edge onto the pads lobs up, Natarajan did so well but failed to take it

Cummins to Gaikwad, FOUR, superb from Gaikwad. A low full-toss outside off, Gaikwad reaches for it and opens the face of the bat to slice it between backward point and short third man

They are now checking for the height on this. Mitchell has been asked to wait. And he has been given out as the umps have a word with him. The partnership is broken.
